        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Even if set to 1 the fact that the wrong line is being kept means there's still a bug to be fixed, but it seems like the return is not worth the investment.\r\n\r\nAnyway I just wanted to highlight that not being able to clear the scrollback buffer is definitely annoying and results in bad UX. It's a really minor issue, but it bugs me and thousand other people that use Neovim as their terminal emulator.\r\n\r\nIf I could have some pointers on where to address this, potentially supporting a scrollback of 0 or even adding a native way of clearing the scrollback buffer completely, I would be happy to put a PR to address this. Let me know!",
